meanings.definition: To push out or force out.
meanings.sent1: She tried to outpush the heavy door to escape the room.
meanings.sent2: The strong wind outpushed the clouds, revealing the bright sun.
meanings.sent3: The little bird outpushed the big bird in the race to the feeder.
meanings.sent4: His determination to succeed outpushed any obstacles in his way.
meanings.sent5: The water pressure was so strong that it seemed to outpush the dam itself.

meanings.definition: The act of pushing out or forcing out.
meanings.sent1: The outpush of air from the balloon made it fly high in the sky.
meanings.sent2: The outpush of water from the hose helped put out the fire.
meanings.sent3: The outpush of students from the classroom at the end of the day was chaotic.
meanings.sent4: The outpush of emotions overwhelmed her as she watched the touching movie.
meanings.sent5: The outpush of energy from the sun keeps our planet warm and alive.
